race.comment: SUPER COOL (2) is rarely far away but tends to find one better, placing 21 from 39 starts. Finished in the minors last time when second (22.50) at this track making it back to back placings. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Deserves a win and gets his chance. SIN CITY MARV (5) doesn't win out of turn but looks close to breaking through. Continues to race well, filling the minors at the last three starts, the latest when third (22.76) at this track. Solid record here winning two races. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings four times from six attempts. Leading chance. CHIEF WIGGUM (8) collided with another runner and finished a well held 6 lengths sixth (17.77) last time in a Grade 5/6 at this track over 300m. May be worth another try. GETTIN' TIPSY (1) can find the frame without surprising.
